---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Anaesthetics — Curriculum" description="ANZCA anaesthesia training curriculum — Roles in Practice, Clinical Fundamentals, and Specialised Study Units.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Curriculum</h1>
    <p>Anaesthetics — ANZCA</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>7 Roles in Practice</h2>
    <p>The professional competency framework underpinning the entire program.</p>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li><strong>Medical Expert</strong> — Clinical knowledge, technical skills, and professional attitudes for anaesthetic practice</li>
      <li><strong>Communicator</strong> — Communicating with staff, patients, and families; building therapeutic relationships</li>
      <li><strong>Collaborator</strong> — Functioning effectively within healthcare teams and interdisciplinary environments</li>
      <li><strong>Leader and Manager</strong> — Managing personal development, healthcare teams, and broader healthcare systems</li>
      <li><strong>Health Advocate</strong> — Advancing the health of patients and community through professional practice</li>
      <li><strong>Scholar</strong> — Teaching, learning, research, evidence evaluation, audit and quality improvement</li>
      <li><strong>Professional</strong> — Ethical practice, personal behaviour, and profession-led regulation</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>7 Clinical Fundamentals</h2>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li>Airway management</li>
      <li>General anaesthesia & sedation</li>
      <li>Pain medicine</li>
      <li>Perioperative medicine</li>
      <li>Regional & local anaesthesia</li>
      <li>Resuscitation, trauma & crisis management</li>
      <li>Safety & quality in anaesthetic practice</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Specialised Study Units (SSUs)</h2>
    <p>Completed during Advanced Training.</p>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li>Cardiac surgery</li>
      <li>General / urological / gynaecological procedures</li>
      <li>Head & neck</li>
      <li>Intensive care <span class="tag">min. 11 weeks at CICM-accredited unit</span></li>
      <li>Neurosurgery</li>
      <li>Obstetrics</li>
      <li>Ophthalmic</li>
      <li>Orthopaedic</li>
      <li>Paediatric</li>
      <li>Plastic / burns</li>
      <li>Thoracic</li>
      <li>Vascular surgery</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Patient Clinical Interaction Assessment (PCIA)</h2>
    <p>Introduced 2025. Observation of trainee interacting with a real patient in a clinical setting.</p>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li>Assesses history-taking, physical examination, perioperative risk understanding</li>
      <li>Required for ASA III+ complexity patients at consultant level</li>
      <li>Must complete before progressing to Provisional Fellowship</li>
      <li>Unlimited attempts — unsuccessful attempts not recorded in MyPortfolio</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>
